Installation instructions for jlirc


Requirements

Linux:

	- a Java Runtime Enviroment (JRE) (>= 1.2.2)

	- LIRC (http://www.lirc.org/) should be installed and running for you to be able
	  to use jlirc

Windows:
	- a Java Runtime Enviroment (JRE) (>= 1.2.2)

	- WinLIRC (http://home.jtan.com/~jim/winlirc/) should be installed and running for you
	  to be able to use jlirc



Installing

Put the 'org' directory somewhere on your CLASSPATH (or add its location to the CLASSPATH)
